kbdrgb is a simple way to change the color scheme of your keyboard
------------------------------------------------------------------

Please make sure that your system has the `/sys/class/leds/kbd_backlight/multi_intensity` file. If not, or if there are other options available, please report it as an issue or do a pull request to add support for more keyboard types!


Usage
-----

To use kbdrgb, simply run the command:
`kbdrgb <color>`

For example, `kbdrgb '0 255 55'` will set the color to emerald.